   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="poem">
            <head><title>"Siren Song"</title></head>

            <lg n="1">
               <l>This is the one song everyone</l>
               <l>would like to learn: the song</l>
               <l>that is irresistible:</l>
            </lg>

            <lg n="2">
               <l>the song that forces men</l>
               <l> to leap overboard in squadrons</l>
               <l> even though they see beached skulls</l>
            </lg>

            <lg n="3">
               <l>the song nobody knows</l>
               <l>because anyone who had heard it</l>
               <l>is dead, and the others can’t remember.</l>
               <l>Shall I tell you the secret</l>
               <l>and if I do, will you get me</l>
               <l>out of this bird suit?</l>
               <l>I don’t enjoy it here</l>
               <l>squatting on this island</l>
               <l>looking picturesque and mythical</l>
               <l>with these two feathery maniacs,</l>
               <l>I don’t enjoy singing</l>
               <l>this trio, fatal and valuable.</l>
            </lg>

            <lg n="4">
               <l>I will tell the secret to you,</l>
               <l>to you, only to you.</l>
               <l>Come closer. This song</l>
            </lg>

            <lg n="5">
               <l>is a cry for help: Help me!</l>
               <l>Only you, only you can,</l>
               <l>you are unique</l>
            </lg>

            <lg n="6">
               <l>at last. Alas</l>
               <l>it is a boring song</l>
               <l>but it works every time.</l>
            </lg>

         </div>

         <byline><persName xml:id="matw01">Margaret Atwood</persName><date when-iso="2003-01-03">Friday, January 3, 2003</date></byline>
         <!-- Hi class -->
      </body>
